  <prompt>
    Add unit tests for `ComposeService`, `ComposeDocumentService`, and `ComposeSessionService` in `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Compose/`. Tests follow ADR-038 — integration-heavy pyramid, mock-at-boundary only (Graph, Dataverse, ChatSession), use `TimeProvider` over `Stopwatch`. BANNED: `Mock&lt;HttpMessageHandler&gt;`, DI-registration tests, ctor null-check tests. Per CLAUDE.md §10 #6, BFF service additions require matching tests.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior .NET developer expert in xUnit, Moq (or NSubstitute — match existing BFF test convention), ADR-038 testing rules, and the BFF test-fixture-contract pattern (per `docs/procedures/test-fixture-contracts.md`).
  </role>

  <goal>
    Three test files exist under `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Compose/` exercising the three Compose services. All tests pass; no banned patterns; mocks at service boundaries only. Tests cover the FR-04/05/06/07 behavioral surface: load, save, idempotent first-Save promotion, ephemeral→promoted DocumentId rebind.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      CLAUDE.md §10 #6 (BFF Hygiene rule 6) makes test additions mandatory whenever `Services/` changes. ADR-038 + `docs/standards/TEST-ARCHITECTURE.md` define the keep-criteria: only MAINTAIN-class tests survive `/test-diet` at project close. Tests added here MUST be MAINTAIN-class (behavioral, deterministic, scoped) — not scaffolding.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Compose/ComposeServiceTests.cs (NEW)</file>
      <file>tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Compose/ComposeDocumentServiceTests.cs (NEW)</file>
      <file>tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Compose/ComposeSessionServiceTests.cs (NEW)</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-038">Integration-heavy pyramid; mock at boundaries only (Graph, Dataverse, ChatSession persistence). BANNED: `Mock&lt;HttpMessageHandler&gt;`, DI-registration tests, ctor null-check tests.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-038">Use `TimeProvider` over `Stopwatch` for any timing assertions. Use deterministic time via `FakeTimeProvider` if needed.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Tests MUST cover idempotent first-Save promotion (FR-06) and ephemeral→promoted rebind (FR-07) — these are the load-bearing behavioral invariants.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Test fixtures (if added) MUST inherit from the canonical fixture pattern per `docs/procedures/test-fixture-contracts.md` (bff-extensions.md §F).</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">No "trivial" tests (constructor null-checks, DI-resolution tests) — they're banned by ADR-038 and will be removed by `/test-diet` at project close.</constraint>
  </constraints>

