  <steps>
    <step order="0" name="Context check + load knowledge">Verify context &lt; 70%. Load ADR-038, TEST-ARCHITECTURE.md (6 KEEP categories), testing.md constraints, and the three new Compose service files for surface to exercise.</step>
    <step order="1" name="Scaffold ComposeServiceTests.cs">Add tests for: (a) `PromoteIfEphemeralAsync` returns existing id when already promoted; (b) `PromoteIfEphemeralAsync` creates a new `sprk_documentid` once and is idempotent on second call; (c) `SaveAsync` delegates to `IComposeDocumentService.SaveDocxAsync`. Use mocks at boundaries; do NOT mock internal collaborators.</step>
    <step order="2" name="Scaffold ComposeDocumentServiceTests.cs">Add tests for: (a) `LoadDocxAsync` returns expected bytes given a mocked `IGraphClientFactory` returning a stubbed drive-item; (b) `SaveDocxAsync` commits a new version and returns the version id; (c) write paths follow the OBO-vs-MI rule per bff-extensions.md §D. Do NOT use `Mock&lt;HttpMessageHandler&gt;` — mock the Graph client factory abstraction instead.</step>
    <step order="3" name="Scaffold ComposeSessionServiceTests.cs">Add tests for: (a) `EnsureSessionForDocumentAsync` returns a ChatSession with correct DocumentId; (b) `RebindToDocumentIdAsync` is idempotent — second call is a no-op (verify by spy/counter on the underlying session manager); (c) tenant scope inherited from underlying ChatSessionManager (assert tenant flows through).</step>
    <step order="4" name="Run tests">`dotnet test tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/ --filter "FullyQualifiedName~Services.Compose"` — must be green.</step>
    <step order="5" name="ADR-038 conformance grep">Grep test files for banned patterns: `Mock&lt;HttpMessageHandler&gt;`, DI-registration assertions, constructor null-check tests. Must return zero hits.</step>
    <step order="6" name="Measure publish-size (BFF unchanged)">`dotnet publish -c Release src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/`; report compressed delta vs ~45.65 MB baseline (expect 0 MB — tests don't affect BFF publish).</step>
    <step order="7" name="Update TASK-INDEX">Update `tasks/TASK-INDEX.md`: change task 026 status to ✅. Reset `current-task.md`.</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="dotnet">Test, build, publish</tool>
  </tools>

